The dynamic pricing of electricity in Lithuania during this transition period indeed highlights the potential and challenges of relying on renewable sources for grid stability. The episodes of nearly free electricity due to abundant solar and wind generation exemplify the extreme conditions that can arise in a renewable-rich grid. The rapid fluctuation in prices, especially with the NordBalt connection outage, underscores the volatility of renewable energy integration into the broader power market. 

